 of the Chinese Linguistics Project at Princeton University, it sets a new standard for the field. With Classical Chinese: A Basic Reader and its supplementary volumes, Naiying Yuan, Haitao Tang, and James Geiss provide the definitive new resource for students and instructors of classical Chinese language and culture, one whose impact will be lasting.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aChinese languagevReaders. 0aChinese languagevTextbooks for foreign speakersxEnglish. 0aPhilosophy, ChineseyTo 221 B.C. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Chinese.2bisacsh  aAnalects.  aChinese culture.  aChinese philosophy.  aClassical Chinese.  aConfucianism.  aConfucius.  aConscientiousness.  aDeed.  aDichotomy.  aEast Asian studies.  aFilial piety.  aGratitude.  aHarmonious Society.  aIngenuity.  aLaozi.  aMencius.  aMs.  aNoninterference (Buddhism).  aPhilosopher.  aPolitical philosophy.  aPrecept.  aPrinceton University.  aPublication.  aRite.  aRuler.  aSchool of thought.  aSeclusion.  aSuggestion.  aTaoism.  aThe Other Hand.  aWell-being.  aWriting style.1 aGeiss, James, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aTang, Hai-tao, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691189765?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691189765423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691189765/original  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-064977-2  Asian Studies Backlist (2000-